# Development journal

The canonical development journal is **`docs/development-journal.md`**.

## When to read it

Before **planning**, **adding features**, **refactoring**, or **non-trivial fixes**, read recent entries (and any section relevant to the area you are touching). Use it to align with prior decisions, avoid repeating mistakes, and know where related code lives.

## When to update it

After completing work that is **user-visible**, **architectural**, or **hard to infer from code alone**, append an entry at the **top** of the journal (newest first), using the template in that file. Include enough **file paths** and **symbols** that the next change does not require archaeology.

Skip journal entries for purely mechanical edits (typos, formatting, one-line renames with no behavior change) unless they clarify a recurring convention.
